[{"id":"a0ef4a21d25a0f440b3ae1e1d2bff371","from":"J. Epstein","from_email":"jeeproject@yahoo.com","to":"Catherine PARPET","to_list":[{"name":"Catherine PARPET","email":"CPARPET@DARROISVILLEY.COM"}],"cc_list":[],"subject":"Re:","date":"2006-11-27T11:58:34.000Z","formatted_date":"Nov 27, 2006","formatted_time":"11:58 AM","body":"I should be the lender,,, full rights of forclosure,, this should also reduce the valuation for French purposes.. I did not want the town or the press to be able, with the help of friends,(it is France) to make my life uncomfortable..I will  be willing to meet with Chardon and Hottinger,,, but I am not going to be interviewed to simply  buy a house, \n\n----- Original Message ----\nFrom: Catherine PARPET <CPARPET@DARROISVILLEY.COM>\nTo: jeeproject@yahoo.com; Kellens@earthlink.net\nCc: Matthieu DE BOISSESON <MDEBOISSESON@DARROISVILLEY.COM>; Alain MAILLOT <AMAILLOT@DARROISVILLEY.COM>\nSent: Monday, November 27, 2006 6:01:40 AM\nSubject: \n\n\n\n\n \n \n\n\n<!--\n\n /* Style Definitions */\n p.MsoNormal, li.MsoNormal, div.MsoNormal\n\t{margin:0cm;\nmargin-bottom:.0001pt;\nfont-size:12.0pt;\nfont-family:\"Times New Roman\";\ncolor:#003366;}\na:link, span.MsoHyperlink\n\t{color:blue;\ntext-decoration:underline;}\na:visited, span.MsoHyperlinkFollowed\n\t{color:purple;\ntext-decoration:underline;}\nspan.StyleCourrierlectronique17\n\t{font-family:\"Times New Roman\";\ncolor:windowtext;\nfont-weight:normal;\nfont-style:normal;\ntext-decoration:none none;}\n _filtered {\nmargin:70.85pt 70.85pt 70.85pt 70.85pt;}\ndiv.Section1\n\t{}\n-->\n\n\n\n\n\n\nDear\nJeffrey,\n\n\n \n\n\nWe\nunderstand that both you and Juan Pablo Molyneux prefer that the property be sold to Juan Pablo Molyneux only.\n\n\n \n\n\nSince\nMr. Molyneux is a US citizen, we propose to\nset up an acquisition vehicle (very likely a Danish or Luxemburg company), which would enable\nMr. Molyneux to purchase the property\nin the best conditions from a tax standpoint.\n\n\n \n\n\nAfter\nthe sale is completed (for instance, one or two years later), it would be\npossible to proceed with an increase of the stock of this company (which, among\nother possibilities, may allow you to take control of the company).\n\n\n \n\n\nMy\npartner Alain Maillot and I will meet Juan Pablo Molyneux tomorrow, but we shall keep you informed\nof the whole project. I shall be abroad from Tuesday until Sunday, but you may\nget in touch, if you need to, with my partner Alain Maillot, Tel: 01 45 01 52\n72, mobile: 06 07 97 77 34, e-mail address: amaillot@darroisvilley.com.\n\n\n \n\n\nThe\nnotary, Mr. Chardon, has confirmed that\nthere is no legal obstacle to Juan Pablo Molyneux acquiring the property in this manner.\n\n\n \n\n\nKind\nregards,\n\n\n \n\n\nMatthieu\nde BOISS\u00c9SON\n\n\n \n\n\n \n\n\n \n\n\n \n\n\nKind\nregards,\n\n\n \n\n\nMatthieu\nde BOISS\u00c9SON\n\n\n \n\n\n \n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n","body_html":"<html><head><style type=\"text/css\"><!-- DIV {margin:0px;} --></style></head><body><div style=\"font-family:times new roman, new york, times, serif;font-size:12pt\"><div style=\"font-family: times new roman,new york,times,serif; font-size: 12pt;\">I should be the lender,,, full rights of forclosure,, this should also reduce the valuation for French purposes.. I did not want the town or the press to be able, with the help of friends,(it is France) to make my life uncomfortable..I will&nbsp; be willing to meet with Chardon and Hottinger,,, but I am not going to be interviewed to simply&nbsp; buy a house, <br><br><div style=\"font-family: times new roman,new york,times,serif; font-size: 12pt;\">----- Original Message ----<br>From: Catherine PARPET &lt;CPARPET@DARROISVILLEY.COM&gt;<br>To: jeeproject@yahoo.com; Kellens@earthlink.net<br>Cc: Matthieu DE BOISSESON &lt;MDEBOISSESON@DARROISVILLEY.COM&gt;; Alain MAILLOT &lt;AMAILLOT@DARROISVILLEY.COM&gt;<br>Sent: Monday, November 27, 2006\n 6:01:40 AM<br>Subject: <br><br>\n\n\n \n \n\n<style>\n<!--\n\n /* Style Definitions */\n